不像；与…不同；（用于对比）与…不同；非…的特征

不像；与…不同；与…相反；不相似；迥异于
不同的；不相似的；不像的；不相符的；不一致的；相异的；不等同的

1.en: Unlike the UK, China seems to understand that the state has a responsibility to protect the lives of vulnerable and innocent citizens.
1.cn: 不像英国政府，中国明白，国家有责任保护易受伤害和无辜公民的生命。

2.en: Narcissus Unlike most flowers, it is known as the "Ivy Ling Po Fairy, " is one of the top ten flowers.
2.cn: 水仙花不同于一般的花，它被称为“凌波仙子”，是十大名花之一。

3.en: Unlike product innovation which tends to focus on the product, looking from inside the company out to the market.
3.cn: 而产品创新往往倾向于是把重点放在产品上，从公司内部寻找市场。

0.en: Unlike Las Vegas, L.A. doesn't have roads smart enough to move all this traffic. And unlike Dallas, there's no room here to build new freeways.
0.cn: 不像拉斯维加斯，洛杉矶的道路是不够智能的，也不像达拉斯,没有足够空间造高速公路。

1.en: Unlike my mole, which is holding steady at the size of a navy bean.
1.cn: 不像我的痣，一直都跟菜豆那么大。

2.en: And what about Harold Finch and his associates? That's unlike you.
2.cn: 那哈罗德·芬奇和他的帮手呢？这可真不像你。

3.en: But there's good news. Unlike the dinosaurs, we can leave Earth.
3.cn: 但是有好消息，不像恐龙那样，我们可以离开地球。

4.en: She was loyal. And careful. All of this feels extremely unlike her.
4.cn: 她的确很忠诚，小心谨慎，这些都不像她会做的事。

5.en: Unlike this house, the library will be completely quiet, so I can focus on my roommate selection.
5.cn: 不像我们家，图书馆会非常安静，我就可以专心选室友了。

6.en: I understand that, unlike Leonard, they're at the top of their respective fields. Boy, you suck.
6.cn: 我了解到，不像莱纳德，他们都是各自领域的权威人物。你个烂人。

7.en: See, I've been waiting my whole life to be engaged, and unlike some people, I'm only planning on doing this once.
7.cn: 我花了一辈子等着订婚，不像某些人，我只计划做一次。

8.en: Which side do you come down on? I'll let you know after tonight. Unlike some people, I'm going in with an open mind.
8.cn: 你支持哪一种轨距呢？今晚过后我会让你知道，不像某些人，起码我会带着开放的态度去听。

9.en: All that proves is that I'm honest, unlike a president who would use the Department of Justice to target his political opponent for his own personal gain.
9.cn: 这只能证明我的诚实，不像总统那样为了个人利益，利用司法部去攻击他的对手。

10.en: I tried to bench you. You refused. Unlike everyone else in your life, I don't work for you. And due to that fact, we're now in a flying doughnut billions of miles from Earth with no backup. I'm backup. No, you're a stowaway.
10.cn: 我让你别插手的。你不肯。不像你人生中的其他所有人，我不为你工作。因为这个，我们现在在一艘飞行甜甜圈上离地球十万八千里还没有后援。我是后援。不，你是偷渡的。

11.en: A living weapon unlike anything we've ever seen.
11.cn: 一个不同于我们所见过的活武器。

12.en: Hiding from people who needed my help. Unlike you.
12.cn: 躲开那些需要援助的人 你就不一样

13.en: Not unlike the Foot Clan and what they'd like to do to our city.
13.cn: 就像大脚帮对我们城市的所作所为。

14.en: Not me, but, yes, someone did. Not unlike butchering a herd of cattle.
14.cn: 不是我，但是，是的，有人在做。就像在屠宰场里宰畜生。

15.en: You are extraordinary, my sons, unlike anything the world has ever seen.
15.cn: 孩子们，你们是非比寻常的，是世间绝无仅有的。

16.en: I need the one person who, unlike me, learned to see through your bullshit long ago.
16.cn: 我需要那个，和我不一样，早就能看穿你鬼话的人。

17.en: Unlike the nicely embellished fictions on your blog, John, real life is rarely so neat.
17.cn: 和你博客上那些精妙小说不一样，约翰，真实的世界从没那么明了。

18.en: Well Raj, I just want to say that I'd never betray your trust. Unlike Leonard I respect you.
18.cn: 那个，拉杰，我只是想说，我绝不会背叛你，不会像莱纳德那样，我尊重你。

19.en: But unlike Edison, we've got some very impressive technology these days to help with the search.
19.cn: 但和爱迪生不同的是，如今我们有了很专业的技术以帮助寻找能源。
